# Pause Means Full Stop

## Rule

When the user indicates pause/stop/interrupt (e.g. "暂停", "先停", "停止", "中断"), treat it as a hard stop for the current automation chain.

- Stop the current running command or workflow immediately.
- Do not auto-retry, do not continue to next step, and do not start replacement commands.
- Do not keep background jobs running for the same task.
- Return a brief status of what has already completed and what was skipped.
- Wait for explicit user confirmation before resuming any execution.

## Applies To

- Any script execution and multi-step automation flow in this workspace.
